WEBVTT

00:00:00.720 --> 00:00:13.970
What fills you with enthusiasm?

00:00:13.970 --> 00:00:16.969
Do you enjoy talking about tasty food

00:00:16.969 --> 00:00:18.969
or do you speak with enthusiasm

00:00:18.969 --> 00:00:22.969
about the playful antics of your little niece or nephew?

00:00:22.969 --> 00:00:26.969
Reasons for enthusiasm vary from person to person.

00:00:26.969 --> 00:00:30.969
But why might a speaker who loves Jehovah

00:00:30.969 --> 00:00:33.969
and who believes what he's saying

00:00:33.969 --> 00:00:36.969
lack enthusiasm when speaking?

00:00:36.969 --> 00:00:40.969
It's not enough just to prepare what to say.

00:00:40.969 --> 00:00:43.969
We must get our heart involved.

00:00:43.969 --> 00:00:48.969
Think about our listeners and breathe life into our delivery.

00:00:48.969 --> 00:00:53.969
This is important both in the congregation and in the ministry.

00:00:53.969 --> 00:00:58.969
As you watch the following example, consider the question,

00:00:58.969 --> 00:01:04.969
does this sister need more enthusiasm for her subject or less?

00:01:04.969 --> 00:01:06.969
The coming paradise will be wonderful.

00:01:06.969 --> 00:01:08.969
Notice just one of the prophecies in the Bible

00:01:08.969 --> 00:01:11.969
regarding the abundant blessings God has promised.

00:01:11.969 --> 00:01:15.969
It's here at Isaiah 65, 21 and 22.

00:01:15.969 --> 00:01:17.969
They will build houses and live in them,

00:01:17.969 --> 00:01:19.969
and they will plant vineyards and eat their fruitage.

00:01:19.969 --> 00:01:21.969
They will not build for someone else to inhabit,

00:01:21.969 --> 00:01:23.969
nor will they plant for others to eat.

00:01:23.969 --> 00:01:26.969
So how did she do?

00:01:26.969 --> 00:01:30.969
When we speak about the blessings of the new Earth under God's Kingdom,

00:01:30.969 --> 00:01:34.969
we should brim with enthusiasm.

00:01:34.969 --> 00:01:37.969
Enthusiasm is contagious.

00:01:37.969 --> 00:01:40.969
Let's watch another example.

00:01:40.969 --> 00:01:43.969
The coming paradise will be wonderful.

00:01:43.969 --> 00:01:46.969
Notice just one of the prophecies in the Bible

00:01:46.969 --> 00:01:50.969
regarding the abundant blessings God has promised.

00:01:50.969 --> 00:01:55.969
